# Trigger Framework

Trigger is an AI Product Team framework that orchestrates cost-optimized model routing, mandatory quality gates, and automated build-review pipelines. It manages project state through a CLI toolkit and `.trigger/` directory.

## Detecting Trigger Requests

When the user says anything matching the trigger phrases below, follow the corresponding workflow. Read the skill file, read any files it references, then execute its steps.

### Project Initialization

| Trigger phrases | Skill |
|---|---|
| "trigger new project", "start a new project", "initialize project" | `init-project` |

### Milestone Management

| Trigger phrases | Action |
|---|---|
| "trigger new milestone", "start milestone N", "next milestone" | Create a new milestone via CLI `milestone create`, set as active |
| "trigger milestone status", "show milestones" | List milestones via CLI `milestone list` |

### Phase Planning

| Trigger phrases | Skill |
|---|---|
| "trigger plan phase N", "plan the next phase", "create phase" | `plan-phase` |

### Phase Execution

| Trigger phrases | Skill |
|---|---|
| "trigger build phase N", "execute phase N", "build it" | `execute-phase` |

### Single Task

| Trigger phrases | Skill |
|---|---|
| "trigger build task N", "build the next task" | `execute-task` |

### Review

| Trigger phrases | Skill |
|---|---|
| "trigger review", "review the changes" | `review-changes` |

### Progress & Status

| Trigger phrases | Skill |
|---|---|
| "trigger status", "where am I", "what's next" | `progress` |

### Sign-off

| Trigger phrases | Skill |
|---|---|
